{{ref improve|date=May 2016}} {{Infobox Magazine | image_file = IcelandReview.jpg | image_size = 234px | image_caption = 2006 cover for the Design Issue. Design by [[Katrín Ólína]] | company = MD Reykjavík | frequency = Bi-monthly | paid_circulation = | unpaid_circulation = | total_circulation = | language = [[English language|English]] | category = [[Iceland|Icelandic Culture]], [[Politics]], [[Social issues]] | editor = Gréta Sigríður Einarsdóttir | staff_writer = Jóhann Páll Ástvaldsson, Jelena Čirič,
| firstdate = August 1963 | country = [[Iceland]] | website = [http://www.icelandreview.com icelandreview.com] | issn = 0019-1094 }}
'''''Iceland Review''''' is the oldest English-language [[magazine]] about [[Iceland]], having originally been published in August, 1963. Iceland Review also runs a news website which covers current events in Iceland.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.icelandreview.com|title=Iceland Review|website=Iceland Review}}</ref> Since 2009, the online version is offered in [[German language|German]] as well. The Iceland Review magazine publishes reports on Icelandic society, politics, pop culture, music, art, literature, current events, as well as interviews with notable Icelanders, articles on traveling in Iceland, and [[photo essay]]s on Iceland. The magazine is published on a bi-monthly basis.<ref>{{cite book|title=Europe Review 2003/04: The Economic and Business Report|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Hwi0s3I5jLEC&pg=PA179|accessdate=28 May 2016|year=2003|publisher=Kogan Page Publishers|isbn=978-0-7494-4067-1|page=179}}</ref>
