{{Italic title}} '''''School Shock''''', also known as ''Chu Feng B.E.E'' ({{zh|t=雛蜂|s=雏蜂|p=Chú Fēng|j=Co1 Fung1}}), {{nihongo||雛蜂|Hinabachi|lead=yes}}, often stylized '''''雛蜂-B.E.E-''''', is a Chinese [[manhua]] and [[animated series]]. Originally a [[science fiction|sci-fi]] [[webcomic]], ''School Shock'' was adapted into an animation when it gained popularity.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Chinese Figure Animation Gets Japanese Dub with Kana Hanazawa|url = http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2015-02-03/chinese-figure-animation-gets-japanese-dub-with-kana-hanazawa/.84054|website = Anime News Network|accessdate = 2015-12-11|date = 2015-02-03}}</ref>
The series began airing in China on July 23, 2015 and in Japan on August 15, 2015.<ref>{{Cite web|title = 「雛蜂－ＢＥＥ－」、中国国産アニメとして日本に初進出|url = http://www.excite.co.jp/News/chn_soc/20150722/Xinhua_24160.html|website = エキサイトニュース|accessdate = 2015-12-11|date = 2015-07-22}}</ref> It is the first Chinese-made animated series to be broadcast simultaneously in China (in [[Standard Chinese|Mandarin]]) and Japan (in [[Japanese language|Japanese]]). Japanese critics described the series as Japanese [[anime]] produced in China and lacking Chinese creative elements.<ref>{{Cite web|title = 国产动画《雏蜂》在日本播出 被批抄袭无中国风格|url = http://fun.youth.cn/2015/0817/1742265.shtml|website = 中国青年网|accessdate = 2015-12-11|date = 2015-08-17|language = Chinese}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = 国漫《雏蜂》遭日本差评山寨 作者回应|url = http://news.mydrivers.com/1/443/443415.htm?v1|website = 驱动之家|accessdate = 2015-12-22|language = Chinese|date = 2015-08-20}}</ref>
''School Shock'' comic books have also been published in [[Simplified Chinese characters|Simplified Chinese]] by a [[Jilin]] publisher,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://book.douban.com/series/9365|title=雏蜂|publisher=[[Douban]]|accessdate=2015-12-11}}</ref> and in [[Traditional Chinese characters|Traditional Chinese]] by a [[Hong Kong]] publisher.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://book.douban.com/series/10280|title=雛蜂|publisher=[[Douban]]|accessdate=2015-12-11}}</ref>
